    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.1-3_0001"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">1</fw>
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS
                    
                    ∙THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS∙</hi>
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A Winged Horse</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    25<hi rend="italics">th</hi> <hi rend="caps">YEAR
                    1934 ∙ 1959
                    
                    890 PARK AVENUE NEW YORK 21, N. Y.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>April 8, 1959</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Professor and <unclear/> Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>You have long been a friend of The Academy of American Poets and its activities. Your interest has meant more than we can ever say. It is measurable only in the achievements which we proudly proclaim, and which your help has made possible.</p>
                
                <p>In celebration of The Academy's 25th Anniversary we are planning a most outstanding literary Dinner. It is to be held in the Ballroom of the Hotel Waldorf Astoria on Wednesday evening, November 4th, 1959. We expect to have an exciting program and can promise you an unforgettable evening.</p>
                
                <p><del>In order to assure the same high quality and the same success of all the previous Dinners, Benefits and other events, we need you with us as never before! May we include your name amongst our Patrons? This entails no obligation other than the taking of two or more tickets. These are expected to be priced at $25 apiece, and are wholly tax deductible. Tables will seat eight or ten.</del></p>
                    
                <p><del>Will you honor us again? You know how much we would appreciate your filling in and returning the enclosed postcard at your earliest convenience. Our Patrons, of course, receive preferred placement.</del></p>          
                <closer>
                    <salute>Most sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>Marie Bullock</signed>
                
                    <signed>Mrs. Hugh Bullock
                    President</signed>
                </closer>
                
                <postscript>
                    <p>This will bring you the news of the climax of <unclear>our</unclear> Anniversary year Please <hi rend="underline">surely</hi> plan to be with us as <unclear>our</unclear> <hi rend="underline">Guests of Honor</hi>, and do help by spreading the word!</p>
                </postscript>
                
            </div1>
            
            
            <div1 type="enclosure">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.27a.1-3_0002"/>
                
                <fw type="curatorial">2</fw>
                
                <hi rend="caps">THE ACADEMY OF AMERICAN POETS</hi>
                <hi rend="italics">25th Anniversary Dinner</hi>
                November 4th, 1959
                
                I shall be a Patron
                Please reserve............places at $25.00.
                I cannot be a Patron, but will take.........tickets
                <hi rend="caps">NAME</hi>................................................
                (As you wish to be listed on invitation)
                <hi rend="caps">ADDRESS</hi>.............................................
                .......................................<hi rend="caps">PHONE</hi>........
                I cannot attend, but enclose a contribution of $....
                for the 25th anniversary.
                (Please make checks payable to Thomas <hi rend="caps">J.</hi> Watson, Jr., Treasurer)
                
            </div1>
            
            
